## Who is a PR Manager?
A PR manager (public relations manager) is a media and public relations specialist responsible for planning and directing the creation of materials in order to support or improve the public image of their employer or client.## Responsibilities of the PR Manager include:
 The responsibilities of the PR manager vacancy will include:
* Working with online publications around the world;
* Publishing or posting promotional materials and reviews about our company;
* Analysis of site owners according to the indicators we provided and work with spreadsheet applications;
* Organization of work on public relations and mass media.

You will master skills such as analyzing the quality of media resources, types of audiences, and proficiency in online analysis tools. If you already have such skills, it will be a big benefit.## Basic requirements for a PR Manager are:
* Understanding the principle of content creation – from ordinary texts to multimedia;
* Excellent command of written and spoken English;
* Be advanced enough to work with social media;
* PC proficiency (MS Office, Google Drive, Data Search).
To apply for this position, you will need to record a [videointerview](/videointerview) in English and complete a test task. We will be happy to consider your candidacy.
